1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15.1-06 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to policies for student cellular telephone use.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15.1-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Cellular telephone usage policy.
7 1. As used in this section:
8 a. "Cellular telephone" means a wireless communication device , which is capable o f
9 transmitting voice, text, or data between parties. The term does not include a
10 table t , laptop compute r , or personal computer approved by the school district for
11 educational use.
12 b. "Instructional time" means the time when a student is attending class or an
13 educational activity.
14 c. "Noninstructional time" means the time when a student is not attending class or
15 an educational activity, including lunch, recess, time between classes, the time
16 before a student's first class and after a student's last class, and open class
17 periods.
18 2. A board of a school district shall adopt a policy governing the use of cellular
19 telephones during instructional and noninstructional time.
20 3. A policy:
21 a. May include time and location restrictions for cellular telephone usage, limitations
22 regarding disruptions, proper instructional use, acceptable and unacceptable use
