1 of cellular telephones for students and staff, and disciplinary actions for student
2 noncompliance.
3 b. Must include exceptions for:
4 (1) Medical accommodations. An individual may use a cellular telephone or
5 other technological device, if required for accommodations based on a
6 disability or management of a medical condition, including continuous
7 glucose monitoring or seizure alerts. The individual shall provide to the
8 school administrator relevant documentation from a licensed health care
9 provider.
10 (2) Educational accommodations. A student with an individual education
11 program, individual learning plan, a plan under section 504 of the
12 Rehabilitation Act of 1973 [29 U.S.C. 794], or other plan under the law must
13 be accommodated according to the plan.
14 (3) Emergency situations affecting the health, safety, or well-being of a student
15 or staff member.
